e head of Perseverance Creek. The sawmill and tramway closed in 1936.<ref name=qpnl/>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of tramways in Queensland]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Toowoomba Region}}\n\n[[Category:Toowoomba Region]]\n[[Category:Localities in Queensland]]\n\n\n{{Toowoomba-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2017}}\n{{Use Australian English|date=December 2017}}\n{{Infobox Australian place\n| type                = suburb\n| name                = Palmtree\n| city                = \n| state               = qld\n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| coordinates         = {{coord|-27.4066|152.1486|type:city_region:AU-QLD|display=inline,title}}\n| pop                 = \n| pop_year            = \n| pop_footnotes       = \n| established         = \n| postcode            = 4352\n| area                = 46.5\n| dist1               = \n| dir1                = \n| location1           = \n| dist2               = \n| dir2                = \n| location2           = \n| dist3               = \n| dir3                = \n| location3           = \n| dist4               = \n| dir4                = \n| location4           =\n| lga                 = Toowoomba Region\n| stategov            = [[Electoral district of Condamine|Condamine]]\n| fedgov              = [[Division of Maranoa|Maranoa]]\n| near-n              = [[Ravensbourne, Queensland|Ravensbourne]]\n| near-ne             = [[Buaraba, Queensland|Buaraba]]\n| near-e              = [[Buaraba South, Queensland|Buaraba South]]\n| near-se             = [[Seventeen Mile, Queensland|Seventeen Mile]]\n| near-s              = [[Seventeen Mile, Queensland|Seventeen Mile]]\n| near-sw             = [[White Mountain, Queensland|White Mountain]]\n| near-w              = [[Hampton, Queensland|Hampton]]\n| near-nw             = [[Perseverance, Queensland|Perseverance]]\n}}\n'''Palmtree''' is a [[Suburbs and localities (Australia)|locality]] in the [[Toowoomba Region]], [[Queensland]], Australia.<ref name=qpnl>{{cite QPN|48032|Palmtree|locality in Toowoomba Region|accessdate=8 November 2017}}</ref>\n\n== History ==\nThe locality takes its name from  State School name first used 1901, for the settlement at the terminus of the Hampton Timber Tramway to the head of Perseverance Creek. The sawmill and tramway closed in 1936.<ref name=qpnl/>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of tramways in Queensland]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{Toowoomba Region}}\n\n[[Category:Toowoomba Region]]\n[[Category:Localities in Queensland]]\n\n\n{{Queensland-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "SDZeroBot", "label": "safe", "comment": "Stub sorting: replacing Queensland-geo-stub with Toowoomba-geo-stub", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palmtree,_Queensland"}
{"title_page": "Watling Island, Bermuda", "text_new": "#redirect[[List of islands of Bermuda]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n'''Watling Island''' is an [[List of islands of Bermuda|island]] in the [[Great Sound]] of [[Bermuda]]. It is 130 meters long in a northwest-southeast direction, and in the northwestern part up to 55 meters wide, yielding a surface area of approximately one acre (0.4 hectares). It is part of [[Warwick Parish]].\n\n{{coord|32|17|7|N|64|48|26|W|display=title|type:isle_source:GNS-enwiki}}\n\n[[Category:Islands of Bermuda]]\n[[Category:Warwick Parish]]\n\n\n{{Bermuda-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Reywas92", "label": "safe", "comment": "Unsourced, failsWP:NGEO,WP:NOPAGE", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Watling_Island,_Bermuda&redirect=no"}
